	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?item=30780&mid=109984059769224>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?item=30780&mid=109984059769224>charm effects</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?item=30780&mid=109984059769224#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Sun, Nov 7th 10:16 AM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=85584><span id=Sage>barfly</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>163 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [3.70]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Although it has a recommended level (60), the stats are at full value from level 1.<br><br>I have these on my two iksars (monk and SK) and they are great because they can just forage occasionally and maintain the stats without getting too hungry.&nbsp;&nbsp;I do have to eat periodically to stave off the adverse effects of hunger, although I have not yet found a point at which I can eat and maintain stats.  For example, after seeing a few messages telling me that I am hungery, I will forage someting and consume it, losing my stats, but just for a few minutes.  I imagine there is a point at which I could avoid the negative effects of hunger while maintaining the potency of the charm, but I have not figured that out yet (too lazy to time this stuff).<br><br>Excellent piece of equipment for those races (iksar, wood elf) and classes (ranger, bard) that can forage.  Beastlords would also have an easy time managing hunger since they can summon food.  Other melee and hybrid classes would have to learn to bake and carry around a collapsible spit with inedible ingredients, which could be a hassle (edible goo is an obvious choice now that fire beetle eyes are stackable).<br><br>Great charm for those who can use it, and usually much cheaper than those with lesser stats and wierd requirements.</p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
